# Git: No Push

**Never run `git push`** or any variant (`git push --force`, `git push --force-with-lease`, etc.).

The user always pushes to the remote manually. You may:
- Commit changes (`git commit`)
- Stage files (`git add`)
- Suggest the push command for the user to run

Do not execute `git push`.
